  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education Kits for 21,000 children in Pakistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We run community-based SABAQ Centres for highly marginalized and remote communities in Pakistan where children learn only through digital lessons using the SABAQ Tab. However, technology alone can not facilitate the skills development in the children. SABAQ will provide education kits to 21,000 students in 500 Centres in Sindh. Each kit will have English and Urdu readers, practice workbooks and other classroom resources for a holistic classroom experience in a non-formal education set-up.</narrative>
  </description>
